[head=1]BRIGMED RULES[/head]
[head=3]by: Ciro Kolmogorov Malet[/head]
─────────────────────────────────────────────

These rules define how I operate as the sole Brig Medical officer.  
They prioritize safety, efficiency, and proper resource management in all field situations.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
[head=3]PATIENT PRIORITY & FLOW[/head]

- [bold]Command personnel and Security[/bold] always receive attention first.  
- [bold]Prisoners[/bold] are treated only after all Command and Security needs are met.  
- [bold]Normal crewmembers[/bold] should go to MedBay unless an emergency prevents it.  
- [bold]Wait your turn[/bold]; one patient at a time avoids mistakes.  

─────────────────────────────────────────────
[head=3]CONDUCT & RESOURCE MANAGEMENT[/head]

- [bold]No prisoner processing in BrigMed.[/bold] Cuffing allowed; disciplinary discussions must occur outside.  
- [bold]Avoid crowding the area.[/bold] Keep pathways clear for emergencies.  
- [bold]Topicals and consumables are for critical patients only.[/bold]  
- [bold]Follow my instructions.[/bold] I am the sole authority in this space.  
- [bold]Be kind and professional.[/bold] Calm, orderly conduct ensures safety and efficiency.  

─────────────────────────────────────────────
Sincerely,  
Ciro Kolmogorov Malet — Brig Medical
